                    "company": "ASML",
                    "description": "A photolithography tool is essential during the exposure step of manufacturing micro/nano chips.  ILIAS (Integrated Lens Interferometer At Scanner) is a full wavefront measurement system integrated into the TWINSCAN photolithography tool to be able to measure and minimize the aberration of the projection optics during setup and production. Accuracy and repeatibility of ILIAS has direct impact on vital system level parameters such as overlay, imaging and focus. With the help of ILIAS camera illumination pupil can also be measured with sufficient accuracy. \n\nI am an architect/lead design engineer of ILIAS metrology with 7+ years industry experience. I am currently working on EXE:5000 (high NA EUV tool) project to help developing the future generation EUV Lithography tools. This project would enable continuation of Moore's law further. My responsibilities includes:\n\n- Define functional and performance specification at module level to meet system level specifications.\n- Define road map for the upcoming development program after agreement with system engineers and other architects. \n- Interface with interdisciplinary teams regarding technical decisions and specifications\n- Mentor and train new engineers in the image sensor group\n- Technical adviser to project, team and group lead.\n- Sensor and reticle HW design\n- Design for performance improvement and adding more function for interferometer based aberration measurement.\n- Design new tests/ develop existing tests for the sensor.\n- Troubleshoot and investigation of issues.\n- Perform machine tests in Twinscan for qualification.\n- Analyse data and documentation.",
                    "title": "Optical Design Engineer",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
